326 /// Check whether or not we should apply the terminal rule on the ----
327 /// destination (Dst) of \p Copy. ----
328 /// When the terminal rule applies, Copy is not profitable to ----
329 /// coalesce. ----
330 /// Dst is terminal if it has exactly one affinity (Dst, Src) and ----
331 /// at least one interference (Dst, Dst2). If Dst is terminal, the ----
332 /// terminal rule consists in checking that at least one of ----
333 /// interfering node, say Dst2, has an affinity of equal or greater ----
334 /// weight with Src. ----
335 /// In that case, Dst2 and Dst will not be able to be both coalesced ----
336 /// with Src. Since Dst2 exposes more coalescing opportunities than ----
337 /// Dst, we can drop \p Copy. ----
338 bool applyTerminalRule(const MachineInstr &Copy) const; ----

526 // Check our invariants ----
527 assert(Src.isVirtual() && "Src must be virtual"); 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
528 assert(!(Dst.isPhysical() && DstSub) && "Cannot have a physical SubIdx"); 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
529 SrcReg = Src; 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
530 DstReg = Dst; 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
531 return true; 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
532 } ----
533 ----
534 bool CoalescerPair::flip() { 0
535 if (DstReg.isPhysical()) 0
536 return false; 0
537 std::swap(SrcReg, DstReg); 0
538 std::swap(SrcIdx, DstIdx); 0
539 Flipped = !Flipped; 0
540 return true; 0
541 } ----
542 ----
543 bool CoalescerPair::isCoalescable(const MachineInstr *MI) const { 0
544 if (!MI) 0
545 return false; 0
546 Register Src, Dst; 0
547 unsigned SrcSub = 0, DstSub = 0; 0
548 if (!isMoveInstr(TRI, MI, Src, Dst, SrcSub, DstSub)) 0
549 return false; 0
550 ----
551 // Find the virtual register that is SrcReg. ----
552 if (Dst == SrcReg) { 0
553 std::swap(Src, Dst); 0
554 std::swap(SrcSub, DstSub); 0
555 } else if (Src != SrcReg) { 0
556 return false; 0
557 } ----
558 ----
559 // Now check that Dst matches DstReg. ----
560 if (DstReg.isPhysical()) { 0
561 if (!Dst.isPhysical()) 0
562 return false; 0
563 assert(!DstIdx && !SrcIdx && "Inconsistent CoalescerPair state."); 0
564 // DstSub could be set for a physreg from INSERT_SUBREG. ----
565 if (DstSub) 0
566 Dst = TRI.getSubReg(Dst, DstSub); 0
567 // Full copy of Src. ----
568 if (!SrcSub) 0
569 return DstReg == Dst; 0
570 // This is a partial register copy. Check that the parts match. ----
571 return Register(TRI.getSubReg(DstReg, SrcSub)) == Dst; 0
572 } else { ----
573 // DstReg is virtual. ----
574 if (DstReg != Dst) 0
575 return false; 0
576 // Registers match, do the subregisters line up? ----
577 return TRI.composeSubRegIndices(SrcIdx, SrcSub) == 0
578 TRI.composeSubRegIndices(DstIdx, DstSub); 0
579 } ----
580 } ----

586 AU.addPreserved(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
587 AU.addPreserved(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
588 AU.addRequired(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
589 AU.addPreserved(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
590 AU.addPreservedID(MachineDominatorsID); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
591 MachineFunctionPass::getAnalysisUsage(AU); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
592 } 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

608 ----
609 bool RegisterCoalescer::adjustCopiesBackFrom(const CoalescerPair &CP, 0
610 MachineInstr *CopyMI) { ----
611 assert(!CP.isPartial() && "This doesn't work for partial copies."); 0
612 assert(!CP.isPhys() && "This doesn't work for physreg copies."); 0
613 ----
614 LiveInterval &IntA = ----
615 LIS->getInterval(CP.isFlipped() ? CP.getDstReg() : CP.getSrcReg()); 0
616 LiveInterval &IntB = ----
617 LIS->getInterval(CP.isFlipped() ? CP.getSrcReg() : CP.getDstReg()); 0
618 SlotIndex CopyIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(*CopyMI).getRegSlot(); 0
619 ----
620 // We have a non-trivially-coalescable copy with IntA being the source and ----
621 // IntB being the dest, thus this defines a value number in IntB. If the ----
622 // source value number (in IntA) is defined by a copy from B, see if we can ----
623 // merge these two pieces of B into a single value number, eliminating a copy. ----
624 // For example: ----
625 // ----
626 // A3 = B0 ----
627 // ... ----
628 // B1 = A3 <- this copy ----
629 // ----
630 // In this case, B0 can be extended to where the B1 copy lives, allowing the ----
631 // B1 value number to be replaced with B0 (which simplifies the B ----
632 // liveinterval). ----
633 ----
634 // BValNo is a value number in B that is defined by a copy from A. 'B1' in ----
635 // the example above. ----
636 LiveInterval::iterator BS = IntB.FindSegmentContaining(CopyIdx); 0
637 if (BS == IntB.end()) return false; 0
638 VNInfo *BValNo = BS->valno; 0
639 ----
640 // Get the location that B is defined at. Two options: either this value has ----
641 // an unknown definition point or it is defined at CopyIdx. If unknown, we ----
642 // can't process it. ----
643 if (BValNo->def != CopyIdx) return false; 0
644 ----
645 // AValNo is the value number in A that defines the copy, A3 in the example. ----
646 SlotIndex CopyUseIdx = CopyIdx.getRegSlot(true); 0
647 LiveInterval::iterator AS = IntA.FindSegmentContaining(CopyUseIdx); 0
648 // The live segment might not exist after fun with physreg coalescing. ----
649 if (AS == IntA.end()) return false; 0
650 VNInfo *AValNo = AS->valno; 0
651 ----
652 // If AValNo is defined as a copy from IntB, we can potentially process this. ----
653 // Get the instruction that defines this value number. ----
654 MachineInstr *ACopyMI = LIS->getInstructionFromIndex(AValNo->def); 0
655 // Don't allow any partial copies, even if isCoalescable() allows them. ----
656 if (!CP.isCoalescable(ACopyMI) || !ACopyMI->isFullCopy()) 0
657 return false; 0
658 ----
659 // Get the Segment in IntB that this value number starts with. ----
660 LiveInterval::iterator ValS = ----
661 IntB.FindSegmentContaining(AValNo->def.getPrevSlot()); 0
662 if (ValS == IntB.end()) 0
663 return false; 0
664 ----
665 // Make sure that the end of the live segment is inside the same block as ----
666 // CopyMI. ----
667 MachineInstr *ValSEndInst = ----
668 LIS->getInstructionFromIndex(ValS->end.getPrevSlot()); 0
669 if (!ValSEndInst || ValSEndInst->getParent() != CopyMI->getParent()) 0
670 return false; 0
671 ----
672 // Okay, we now know that ValS ends in the same block that the CopyMI ----
673 // live-range starts. If there are no intervening live segments between them ----
674 // in IntB, we can merge them. ----
675 if (ValS+1 != BS) return false; 0
676 ----
677 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Extending: " << printReg(IntB.reg(), TRI)); 0
678 ----
679 SlotIndex FillerStart = ValS->end, FillerEnd = BS->start; 0
680 // We are about to delete CopyMI, so need to remove it as the 'instruction ----
681 // that defines this value #'. Update the valnum with the new defining ----
682 // instruction #. ----
683 BValNo->def = FillerStart; 0
684 ----
685 // Okay, we can merge them. We need to insert a new liverange: ----
686 // [ValS.end, BS.begin) of either value number, then we merge the ----
687 // two value numbers. ----
688 IntB.addSegment(LiveInterval::Segment(FillerStart, FillerEnd, BValNo)); 0
689 ----
690 // Okay, merge "B1" into the same value number as "B0". ----
691 if (BValNo != ValS->valno) 0
692 IntB.MergeValueNumberInto(BValNo, ValS->valno); 0
693 ----
694 // Do the same for the subregister segments. ----
695 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &S : IntB.subranges()) { 0
696 // Check for SubRange Segments of the form [1234r,1234d:0) which can be ----
697 // removed to prevent creating bogus SubRange Segments. ----
698 LiveInterval::iterator SS = S.FindSegmentContaining(CopyIdx); 0
699 if (SS != S.end() && SlotIndex::isSameInstr(SS->start, SS->end)) { 0
700 S.removeSegment(*SS, true); 0
701 continue; 0
702 } ----
703 // The subrange may have ended before FillerStart. If so, extend it. ----
704 if (!S.getVNInfoAt(FillerStart)) { 0
705 SlotIndex BBStart = ----
706 LIS->getMBBStartIdx(LIS->getMBBFromIndex(FillerStart)); 0
707 S.extendInBlock(BBStart, FillerStart); 0
708 } ----
709 VNInfo *SubBValNo = S.getVNInfoAt(CopyIdx); 0
710 S.addSegment(LiveInterval::Segment(FillerStart, FillerEnd, SubBValNo)); 0
711 VNInfo *SubValSNo = S.getVNInfoAt(AValNo->def.getPrevSlot()); 0
712 if (SubBValNo != SubValSNo) 0
713 S.MergeValueNumberInto(SubBValNo, SubValSNo); 0
714 } ----
715 ----
716 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " result = " << IntB << '\n'); 0
717 ----
718 // If the source instruction was killing the source register before the ----
719 // merge, unset the isKill marker given the live range has been extended. ----
720 int UIdx = ValSEndInst->findRegisterUseOperandIdx(IntB.reg(), true); 0
721 if (UIdx != -1) { 0
722 ValSEndInst->getOperand(UIdx).setIsKill(false); 0
723 } ----
724 ----
725 // Rewrite the copy. ----
726 CopyMI->substituteRegister(IntA.reg(), IntB.reg(), 0, *TRI); 0
727 // If the copy instruction was killing the destination register or any ----
728 // subrange before the merge trim the live range. ----
729 bool RecomputeLiveRange = AS->end == CopyIdx; 0
730 if (!RecomputeLiveRange) { 0
731 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &S : IntA.subranges()) { 0
732 LiveInterval::iterator SS = S.FindSegmentContaining(CopyUseIdx); 0
733 if (SS != S.end() && SS->end == CopyIdx) { 0
734 RecomputeLiveRange = true; 0
735 break; 0
736 } ----
737 } ----
738 } ----
739 if (RecomputeLiveRange) 0
740 shrinkToUses(&IntA); 0
741 ----
742 ++numExtends; 0
743 return true; 0
744 } ----
745 ----
746 bool RegisterCoalescer::hasOtherReachingDefs(LiveInterval &IntA, 0
747 LiveInterval &IntB, ----
748 VNInfo *AValNo, ----
749 VNInfo *BValNo) { ----
750 // If AValNo has PHI kills, conservatively assume that IntB defs can reach ----
751 // the PHI values. ----
752 if (LIS->hasPHIKill(IntA, AValNo)) 0
753 return true; 0
754 ----
755 for (LiveRange::Segment &ASeg : IntA.segments) { 0
756 if (ASeg.valno != AValNo) continue; 0
757 LiveInterval::iterator BI = llvm::upper_bound(IntB, ASeg.start); 0
758 if (BI != IntB.begin()) 0
759 --BI; 0
760 for (; BI != IntB.end() && ASeg.end >= BI->start; ++BI) { 0
761 if (BI->valno == BValNo) 0
762 continue; 0
763 if (BI->start <= ASeg.start && BI->end > ASeg.start) 0
764 return true; 0
765 if (BI->start > ASeg.start && BI->start < ASeg.end) 0
766 return true; 0
767 } ----
768 } ----
769 return false; 0
770 } ----
771 ----
772 /// Copy segments with value number @p SrcValNo from liverange @p Src to live ----
773 /// range @Dst and use value number @p DstValNo there. ----
774 static std::pair ----
775 addSegmentsWithValNo(LiveRange &Dst, VNInfo *DstValNo, const LiveRange &Src, 0
776 const VNInfo *SrcValNo) { ----
777 bool Changed = false; 0
778 bool MergedWithDead = false; 0
779 for (const LiveRange::Segment &S : Src.segments) { 0
780 if (S.valno != SrcValNo) 0
781 continue; 0
782 // This is adding a segment from Src that ends in a copy that is about ----
783 // to be removed. This segment is going to be merged with a pre-existing ----
784 // segment in Dst. This works, except in cases when the corresponding ----
785 // segment in Dst is dead. For example: adding [192r,208r:1) from Src ----
786 // to [208r,208d:1) in Dst would create [192r,208d:1) in Dst. ----
787 // Recognized such cases, so that the segments can be shrunk. ----
788 LiveRange::Segment Added = LiveRange::Segment(S.start, S.end, DstValNo); 0
789 LiveRange::Segment &Merged = *Dst.addSegment(Added); 0
790 if (Merged.end.isDead()) 0
791 MergedWithDead = true; 0
792 Changed = true; 0
793 } ----
794 return std::make_pair(Changed, MergedWithDead); 0
795 } ----
796 ----
797 std::pair ----
798 RegisterCoalescer::removeCopyByCommutingDef(const CoalescerPair &CP, 0
799 MachineInstr *CopyMI) { ----
800 assert(!CP.isPhys()); 0
801 ----
802 LiveInterval &IntA = ----
803 LIS->getInterval(CP.isFlipped() ? CP.getDstReg() : CP.getSrcReg()); 0
804 LiveInterval &IntB = ----
805 LIS->getInterval(CP.isFlipped() ? CP.getSrcReg() : CP.getDstReg()); 0
806 ----
807 // We found a non-trivially-coalescable copy with IntA being the source and ----
808 // IntB being the dest, thus this defines a value number in IntB. If the ----
809 // source value number (in IntA) is defined by a commutable instruction and ----
810 // its other operand is coalesced to the copy dest register, see if we can ----
811 // transform the copy into a noop by commuting the definition. For example, ----
812 // ----
813 // A3 = op A2 killed B0 ----
814 // ... ----
815 // B1 = A3 <- this copy ----
816 // ... ----
817 // = op A3 <- more uses ----
818 // ----
819 // ==> ----
820 // ----
821 // B2 = op B0 killed A2 ----
822 // ... ----
823 // B1 = B2 <- now an identity copy ----
824 // ... ----
825 // = op B2 <- more uses ----
826 ----
827 // BValNo is a value number in B that is defined by a copy from A. 'B1' in ----
828 // the example above. ----
829 SlotIndex CopyIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(*CopyMI).getRegSlot(); 0
830 VNInfo *BValNo = IntB.getVNInfoAt(CopyIdx); 0
831 assert(BValNo != nullptr && BValNo->def == CopyIdx); 0
832 ----
833 // AValNo is the value number in A that defines the copy, A3 in the example. ----
834 VNInfo *AValNo = IntA.getVNInfoAt(CopyIdx.getRegSlot(true)); 0
835 assert(AValNo && !AValNo->isUnused() && "COPY source not live"); 0
836 if (AValNo->isPHIDef()) 0
837 return { false, false }; 0
838 MachineInstr *DefMI = LIS->getInstructionFromIndex(AValNo->def); 0
839 if (!DefMI) 0
840 return { false, false }; 0
841 if (!DefMI->isCommutable()) 0
842 return { false, false }; 0
843 // If DefMI is a two-address instruction then commuting it will change the ----
844 // destination register. ----
845 int DefIdx = DefMI->findRegisterDefOperandIdx(IntA.reg()); 0
846 assert(DefIdx != -1); 0
847 unsigned UseOpIdx; ----
848 if (!DefMI->isRegTiedToUseOperand(DefIdx, &UseOpIdx)) 0
849 return { false, false }; 0
850 ----
851 // FIXME: The code below tries to commute 'UseOpIdx' operand with some other ----
852 // commutable operand which is expressed by 'CommuteAnyOperandIndex'value ----
853 // passed to the method. That _other_ operand is chosen by ----
854 // the findCommutedOpIndices() method. ----
855 // ----
856 // That is obviously an area for improvement in case of instructions having ----
857 // more than 2 operands. For example, if some instruction has 3 commutable ----
858 // operands then all possible variants (i.e. op#1<->op#2, op#1<->op#3, ----
859 // op#2<->op#3) of commute transformation should be considered/tried here. ----
860 unsigned NewDstIdx = TargetInstrInfo::CommuteAnyOperandIndex; 0
861 if (!TII->findCommutedOpIndices(*DefMI, UseOpIdx, NewDstIdx)) 0
862 return { false, false }; 0
863 ----
864 MachineOperand &NewDstMO = DefMI->getOperand(NewDstIdx); 0
865 Register NewReg = NewDstMO.getReg(); 0
866 if (NewReg != IntB.reg() || !IntB.Query(AValNo->def).isKill()) 0
867 return { false, false }; 0
868 ----
869 // Make sure there are no other definitions of IntB that would reach the ----
870 // uses which the new definition can reach. ----
871 if (hasOtherReachingDefs(IntA, IntB, AValNo, BValNo)) 0
872 return { false, false }; 0
873 ----
874 // If some of the uses of IntA.reg is already coalesced away, return false. ----
875 // It's not possible to determine whether it's safe to perform the coalescing. ----
876 for (MachineOperand &MO : MRI->use_nodbg_operands(IntA.reg())) { 0
877 MachineInstr *UseMI = MO.getParent(); 0
878 unsigned OpNo = &MO - &UseMI->getOperand(0); 0
879 SlotIndex UseIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(*UseMI); 0
880 LiveInterval::iterator US = IntA.FindSegmentContaining(UseIdx); 0
881 if (US == IntA.end() || US->valno != AValNo) 0
882 continue; 0
883 // If this use is tied to a def, we can't rewrite the register. ----
884 if (UseMI->isRegTiedToDefOperand(OpNo)) 0
885 return { false, false }; 0
886 } ----
887 ----
888 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tremoveCopyByCommutingDef: " << AValNo->def << '\t' 0
889 << *DefMI); ----
890 ----
891 // At this point we have decided that it is legal to do this ----
892 // transformation. Start by commuting the instruction. ----
893 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = DefMI->getParent(); 0
894 MachineInstr *NewMI = ----
895 TII->commuteInstruction(*DefMI, false, UseOpIdx, NewDstIdx); 0
896 if (!NewMI) 0
897 return { false, false }; 0
898 if (IntA.reg().isVirtual() && IntB.reg().isVirtual() && 0
899 !MRI->constrainRegClass(IntB.reg(), MRI->getRegClass(IntA.reg()))) 0
900 return { false, false }; 0
901 if (NewMI != DefMI) { 0
902 LIS->ReplaceMachineInstrInMaps(*DefMI, *NewMI); 0
903 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Pos = DefMI; 0
904 MBB->insert(Pos, NewMI); 0
905 MBB->erase(DefMI); 0
906 } ----
907 ----
908 // If ALR and BLR overlaps and end of BLR extends beyond end of ALR, e.g. ----
909 // A = or A, B ----
910 // ... ----
911 // B = A ----
912 // ... ----
913 // C = killed A ----
914 // ... ----
915 // = B ----
916 ----
917 // Update uses of IntA of the specific Val# with IntB. ----
918 for (MachineOperand &UseMO : 0
919 llvm::make_early_inc_range(MRI->use_operands(IntA.reg()))) { 0
920 if (UseMO.isUndef()) 0
921 continue; 0
922 MachineInstr *UseMI = UseMO.getParent(); 0
923 if (UseMI->isDebugInstr()) { 0
924 // FIXME These don't have an instruction index. Not clear we have enough ----
925 // info to decide whether to do this replacement or not. For now do it. ----
926 UseMO.setReg(NewReg); 0
927 continue; 0
928 } ----
929 SlotIndex UseIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(*UseMI).getRegSlot(true); 0
930 LiveInterval::iterator US = IntA.FindSegmentContaining(UseIdx); 0
931 assert(US != IntA.end() && "Use must be live"); 0
932 if (US->valno != AValNo) 0
933 continue; 0
934 // Kill flags are no longer accurate. They are recomputed after RA. ----
935 UseMO.setIsKill(false); 0
936 if (NewReg.isPhysical()) 0
937 UseMO.substPhysReg(NewReg, *TRI); 0
938 else ----
939 UseMO.setReg(NewReg); 0
940 if (UseMI == CopyMI) 0
941 continue; 0
942 if (!UseMI->isCopy()) 0
943 continue; 0
944 if (UseMI->getOperand(0).getReg() != IntB.reg() || 0
945 UseMI->getOperand(0).getSubReg()) 0
946 continue; 0
947 ----
948 // This copy will become a noop. If it's defining a new val#, merge it into ----
949 // BValNo. ----
950 SlotIndex DefIdx = UseIdx.getRegSlot(); 0
951 VNInfo *DVNI = IntB.getVNInfoAt(DefIdx); 0
952 if (!DVNI) 0
953 continue; 0
954 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\t\tnoop: " << DefIdx << '\t' << *UseMI); 0
955 assert(DVNI->def == DefIdx); 0
956 BValNo = IntB.MergeValueNumberInto(DVNI, BValNo); 0
957 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &S : IntB.subranges()) { 0
958 VNInfo *SubDVNI = S.getVNInfoAt(DefIdx); 0
959 if (!SubDVNI) 0
960 continue; 0
961 VNInfo *SubBValNo = S.getVNInfoAt(CopyIdx); 0
962 assert(SubBValNo->def == CopyIdx); 0
963 S.MergeValueNumberInto(SubDVNI, SubBValNo); 0
964 } ----
965 ----
966 deleteInstr(UseMI); 0
967 } ----
968 ----
969 // Extend BValNo by merging in IntA live segments of AValNo. Val# definition ----
970 // is updated. ----
971 bool ShrinkB = false; 0
972 BumpPtrAllocator &Allocator = LIS->getVNInfoAllocator(); 0
973 if (IntA.hasSubRanges() || IntB.hasSubRanges()) { 0
974 if (!IntA.hasSubRanges()) { 0
975 LaneBitmask Mask = MRI->getMaxLaneMaskForVReg(IntA.reg()); 0
976 IntA.createSubRangeFrom(Allocator, Mask, IntA); 0
977 } else if (!IntB.hasSubRanges()) { 0
978 LaneBitmask Mask = MRI->getMaxLaneMaskForVReg(IntB.reg()); 0
979 IntB.createSubRangeFrom(Allocator, Mask, IntB); 0
980 } ----
981 SlotIndex AIdx = CopyIdx.getRegSlot(true); 0
982 LaneBitmask MaskA; 0
983 const SlotIndexes &Indexes = *LIS->getSlotIndexes(); 0
984 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &SA : IntA.subranges()) { 0
985 VNInfo *ASubValNo = SA.getVNInfoAt(AIdx); 0
986 // Even if we are dealing with a full copy, some lanes can ----
987 // still be undefined. ----
988 // E.g., ----
989 // undef A.subLow = ... ----
990 // B = COPY A <== A.subHigh is undefined here and does ----
991 // not have a value number. ----
992 if (!ASubValNo) 0
993 continue; 0
994 MaskA |= SA.LaneMask; 0
995 ----
996 IntB.refineSubRanges( 0
997 Allocator, SA.LaneMask, ----
998 [&Allocator, &SA, CopyIdx, ASubValNo, 0
999 &ShrinkB](LiveInterval::SubRange &SR) { 0
1000 VNInfo *BSubValNo = SR.empty() ? SR.getNextValue(CopyIdx, Allocator) 0
1001 : SR.getVNInfoAt(CopyIdx); 0
1002 assert(BSubValNo != nullptr); 0
1003 auto P = addSegmentsWithValNo(SR, BSubValNo, SA, ASubValNo); 0
1004 ShrinkB |= P.second; 0
1005 if (P.first) 0
1006 BSubValNo->def = ASubValNo->def; 0
1007 }, 0
1008 Indexes, *TRI); 0
1009 } ----
1010 // Go over all subranges of IntB that have not been covered by IntA, ----
1011 // and delete the segments starting at CopyIdx. This can happen if ----
1012 // IntA has undef lanes that are defined in IntB. ----
1013 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &SB : IntB.subranges()) { 0
1014 if ((SB.LaneMask & MaskA).any()) 0
1015 continue; 0
1016 if (LiveRange::Segment *S = SB.getSegmentContaining(CopyIdx)) 0
1017 if (S->start.getBaseIndex() == CopyIdx.getBaseIndex()) 0
1018 SB.removeSegment(*S, true); 0
1019 } ----
1020 } ----
1021 ----
1022 BValNo->def = AValNo->def; 0
1023 auto P = addSegmentsWithValNo(IntB, BValNo, IntA, AValNo); 0
1024 ShrinkB |= P.second; 0
1025 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\t\textended: " << IntB << '\n'); 0
1026 ----
1027 LIS->removeVRegDefAt(IntA, AValNo->def); 0
1028 ----
1029 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\t\ttrimmed: " << IntA << '\n'); 0
1030 ++numCommutes; 0
1031 return { true, ShrinkB }; 0
1032 } ----
1033 ----
1034 /// For copy B = A in BB2, if A is defined by A = B in BB0 which is a ----
1035 /// predecessor of BB2, and if B is not redefined on the way from A = B ----
1036 /// in BB0 to B = A in BB2, B = A in BB2 is partially redundant if the ----
1037 /// execution goes through the path from BB0 to BB2. We may move B = A ----
1038 /// to the predecessor without such reversed copy. ----
1039 /// So we will transform the program from: ----
1040 /// BB0: ----
1041 /// A = B; BB1: ----
1042 /// ... ... ----
1043 /// / \ / ----
1044 /// BB2: ----
1045 /// ... ----
1046 /// B = A; ----
1047 /// ----
1048 /// to: ----
1049 /// ----
1050 /// BB0: BB1: ----
1051 /// A = B; ... ----
1052 /// ... B = A; ----
1053 /// / \ / ----
1054 /// BB2: ----
1055 /// ... ----
1056 /// ----
1057 /// A special case is when BB0 and BB2 are the same BB which is the only ----
1058 /// BB in a loop: ----
1059 /// BB1: ----
1060 /// ... ----
1061 /// BB0/BB2: ---- ----
1062 /// B = A; | ----
1063 /// ... | ----
1064 /// A = B; | ----
1065 /// |------- ----
1066 /// | ----
1067 /// We may hoist B = A from BB0/BB2 to BB1. ----
1068 /// ----
1069 /// The major preconditions for correctness to remove such partial ----
1070 /// redundancy include: ----
1071 /// 1. A in B = A in BB2 is defined by a PHI in BB2, and one operand of ----
1072 /// the PHI is defined by the reversed copy A = B in BB0. ----
1073 /// 2. No B is referenced from the start of BB2 to B = A. ----
1074 /// 3. No B is defined from A = B to the end of BB0. ----
1075 /// 4. BB1 has only one successor. ----
1076 /// ----
1077 /// 2 and 4 implicitly ensure B is not live at the end of BB1. ----
1078 /// 4 guarantees BB2 is hotter than BB1, so we can only move a copy to a ----
1079 /// colder place, which not only prevent endless loop, but also make sure ----
1080 /// the movement of copy is beneficial. ----
1081 bool RegisterCoalescer::removePartialRedundancy(const CoalescerPair &CP, 0
1082 MachineInstr &CopyMI) { ----
1083 assert(!CP.isPhys()); 0
1084 if (!CopyMI.isFullCopy()) 0
1085 return false; 0
1086 ----
1087 MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *CopyMI.getParent(); 0
1088 // If this block is the target of an invoke/inlineasm_br, moving the copy into ----
1089 // the predecessor is tricker, and we don't handle it. ----
1090 if (MBB.isEHPad() || MBB.isInlineAsmBrIndirectTarget()) 0
1091 return false; 0
1092 ----
1093 if (MBB.pred_size() != 2) 0
1094 return false; 0
1095 ----
1096 LiveInterval &IntA = ----
1097 LIS->getInterval(CP.isFlipped() ? CP.getDstReg() : CP.getSrcReg()); 0
1098 LiveInterval &IntB = ----
1099 LIS->getInterval(CP.isFlipped() ? CP.getSrcReg() : CP.getDstReg()); 0
1100 ----
1101 // A is defined by PHI at the entry of MBB. ----
1102 SlotIndex CopyIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(CopyMI).getRegSlot(true); 0
1103 VNInfo *AValNo = IntA.getVNInfoAt(CopyIdx); 0
1104 assert(AValNo && !AValNo->isUnused() && "COPY source not live"); 0
1105 if (!AValNo->isPHIDef()) 0
1106 return false; 0
1107 ----
1108 // No B is referenced before CopyMI in MBB. ----
1109 if (IntB.overlaps(LIS->getMBBStartIdx(&MBB), CopyIdx)) 0
1110 return false; 0
1111 ----
1112 // MBB has two predecessors: one contains A = B so no copy will be inserted ----
1113 // for it. The other one will have a copy moved from MBB. ----
1114 bool FoundReverseCopy = false; 0
1115 MachineBasicBlock *CopyLeftBB = nullptr; 0
1116 for (MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB.predecessors()) { 0
1117 VNInfo *PVal = IntA.getVNInfoBefore(LIS->getMBBEndIdx(Pred)); 0
1118 MachineInstr *DefMI = LIS->getInstructionFromIndex(PVal->def); 0
1119 if (!DefMI || !DefMI->isFullCopy()) { 0
1120 CopyLeftBB = Pred; 0
1121 continue; 0
1122 } ----
1123 // Check DefMI is a reverse copy and it is in BB Pred. ----
1124 if (DefMI->getOperand(0).getReg() != IntA.reg() || 0
1125 DefMI->getOperand(1).getReg() != IntB.reg() || 0
1126 DefMI->getParent() != Pred) { 0
1127 CopyLeftBB = Pred; 0
1128 continue; 0
1129 } ----
1130 // If there is any other def of B after DefMI and before the end of Pred, ----
1131 // we need to keep the copy of B = A at the end of Pred if we remove ----
1132 // B = A from MBB. ----
1133 bool ValB_Changed = false; 0
1134 for (auto *VNI : IntB.valnos) { 0
1135 if (VNI->isUnused()) 0
1136 continue; 0
1137 if (PVal->def < VNI->def && VNI->def < LIS->getMBBEndIdx(Pred)) { 0
1138 ValB_Changed = true; 0
1139 break; 0
1140 } ----
1141 } ----
1142 if (ValB_Changed) { 0
1143 CopyLeftBB = Pred; 0
1144 continue; 0
1145 } ----
1146 FoundReverseCopy = true; 0
1147 } ----
1148 ----
1149 // If no reverse copy is found in predecessors, nothing to do. ----
1150 if (!FoundReverseCopy) 0
1151 return false; 0
1152 ----
1153 // If CopyLeftBB is nullptr, it means every predecessor of MBB contains ----
1154 // reverse copy, CopyMI can be removed trivially if only IntA/IntB is updated. ----
1155 // If CopyLeftBB is not nullptr, move CopyMI from MBB to CopyLeftBB and ----
1156 // update IntA/IntB. ----
1157 // ----
1158 // If CopyLeftBB is not nullptr, ensure CopyLeftBB has a single succ so ----
1159 // MBB is hotter than CopyLeftBB. ----
1160 if (CopyLeftBB && CopyLeftBB->succ_size() > 1) 0
1161 return false; 0
1162 ----
1163 // Now (almost sure it's) ok to move copy. ----
1164 if (CopyLeftBB) { 0
1165 // Position in CopyLeftBB where we should insert new copy. ----
1166 auto InsPos = CopyLeftBB->getFirstTerminator(); 0
1167 ----
1168 // Make sure that B isn't referenced in the terminators (if any) at the end ----
1169 // of the predecessor since we're about to insert a new definition of B ----
1170 // before them. ----
1171 if (InsPos != CopyLeftBB->end()) { 0
1172 SlotIndex InsPosIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(*InsPos).getRegSlot(true); 0
1173 if (IntB.overlaps(InsPosIdx, LIS->getMBBEndIdx(CopyLeftBB))) 0
1174 return false; 0
1175 } ----
1176 ----
1177 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tremovePartialRedundancy: Move the copy to " 0
1178 << printMBBReference(*CopyLeftBB) << '\t' << CopyMI); ----
1179 ----
1180 // Insert new copy to CopyLeftBB. ----
1181 MachineInstr *NewCopyMI = BuildMI(*CopyLeftBB, InsPos, CopyMI.getDebugLoc(), 0
1182 TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY), IntB.reg()) 0
1183 .addReg(IntA.reg()); 0
1184 SlotIndex NewCopyIdx = ----
1185 LIS->InsertMachineInstrInMaps(*NewCopyMI).getRegSlot(); 0
1186 IntB.createDeadDef(NewCopyIdx, LIS->getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
1187 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &SR : IntB.subranges()) 0
1188 SR.createDeadDef(NewCopyIdx, LIS->getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
1189 ----
1190 // If the newly created Instruction has an address of an instruction that was ----
1191 // deleted before (object recycled by the allocator) it needs to be removed from ----
1192 // the deleted list. ----
1193 ErasedInstrs.erase(NewCopyMI); 0
1194 } else { ----
1195 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tremovePartialRedundancy: Remove the copy from " 0
1196 << printMBBReference(MBB) << '\t' << CopyMI); ----
1197 } ----
1198 ----
1199 // Remove CopyMI. ----
1200 // Note: This is fine to remove the copy before updating the live-ranges. ----
1201 // While updating the live-ranges, we only look at slot indices and ----
1202 // never go back to the instruction. ----
1203 // Mark instructions as deleted. ----
1204 deleteInstr(&CopyMI); 0
1205 ----
1206 // Update the liveness. ----
1207 SmallVector EndPoints; 0
1208 VNInfo *BValNo = IntB.Query(CopyIdx).valueOutOrDead(); 0
1209 LIS->pruneValue(*static_cast(&IntB), CopyIdx.getRegSlot(), 0
1210 &EndPoints); ----
1211 BValNo->markUnused(); 0
1212 // Extend IntB to the EndPoints of its original live interval. ----
1213 LIS->extendToIndices(IntB, EndPoints); 0
1214 ----
1215 // Now, do the same for its subranges. ----
1216 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &SR : IntB.subranges()) { 0
1217 EndPoints.clear(); 0
1218 VNInfo *BValNo = SR.Query(CopyIdx).valueOutOrDead(); 0
1219 assert(BValNo && "All sublanes should be live"); 0
1220 LIS->pruneValue(SR, CopyIdx.getRegSlot(), &EndPoints); 0
1221 BValNo->markUnused(); 0
1222 // We can have a situation where the result of the original copy is live, ----
1223 // but is immediately dead in this subrange, e.g. [336r,336d:0). That makes ----
1224 // the copy appear as an endpoint from pruneValue(), but we don't want it ----
1225 // to because the copy has been removed. We can go ahead and remove that ----
1226 // endpoint; there is no other situation here that there could be a use at ----
1227 // the same place as we know that the copy is a full copy. ----
1228 for (unsigned I = 0; I != EndPoints.size(); ) { 0
1229 if (SlotIndex::isSameInstr(EndPoints[I], CopyIdx)) { 0
1230 EndPoints[I] = EndPoints.back(); 0
1231 EndPoints.pop_back(); 0
1232 continue; 0
1233 } ----
1234 ++I; 0
1235 } ----
1236 SmallVector Undefs; 0
1237 IntB.computeSubRangeUndefs(Undefs, SR.LaneMask, *MRI, 0
1238 *LIS->getSlotIndexes()); 0
1239 LIS->extendToIndices(SR, EndPoints, Undefs); 0
1240 } 0
1241 // If any dead defs were extended, truncate them. ----
1242 shrinkToUses(&IntB); 0
1243 ----
1244 // Finally, update the live-range of IntA. ----
1245 shrinkToUses(&IntA); 0
1246 return true; 0
1247 } 0
1248 ----
1249 /// Returns true if @p MI defines the full vreg @p Reg, as opposed to just ----
1250 /// defining a subregister. ----
1251 static bool definesFullReg(const MachineInstr &MI, Register Reg) { 0
1252 assert(!Reg.isPhysical() && "This code cannot handle physreg aliasing"); 0
1253 ----
1254 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI.all_defs()) { 0
1255 if (Op.getReg() != Reg) 0
1256 continue; 0
1257 // Return true if we define the full register or don't care about the value ----
1258 // inside other subregisters. ----
1259 if (Op.getSubReg() == 0 || Op.isUndef()) 0
1260 return true; 0
1261 } ----
1262 return false; 0
1263 } ----

1289 } ----

1293 SmallVector NewRegs; 0

1296 return false; 0

1298 if (!definesFullReg(*DefMI, SrcReg)) 0
1299 return false; 0
1300 bool SawStore = false; 0
1301 if (!DefMI->isSafeToMove(AA, SawStore)) 0
1302 return false; 0

1304 if (MCID.getNumDefs() != 1) 0
1305 return false; 0

1313 // the register substantially (beyond both source and dest size). This is bad ----
1314 // for performance since it can cascade through a function, introducing many ----
1315 // extra spills and fills (e.g. ARM can easily end up copying QQQQPR registers ----

1326 DefMI->getOperand(0).getSubReg()); 0

1530 NewMI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateReg( 0
1531 CopyDstReg, true /*IsDef*/, true /*IsImp*/, false /*IsKill*/)); ----
1532 // Record small dead def live-ranges for all the subregisters ----
1533 // of the destination register. ----
1534 // Otherwise, variables that live through may miss some ----
1535 // interferences, thus creating invalid allocation. ----
1536 // E.g., i386 code: ----
1537 // %1 = somedef ; %1 GR8 ----
1538 // %2 = remat ; %2 GR32 ----
1539 // CL = COPY %2.sub_8bit ----
1540 // = somedef %1 ; %1 GR8 ----
1541 // => ----
1542 // %1 = somedef ; %1 GR8 ----
1543 // dead ECX = remat ; implicit-def CL ----
1544 // = somedef %1 ; %1 GR8 ----
1545 // %1 will see the interferences with CL but not with CH since ----
1546 // no live-ranges would have been created for ECX. ----
1547 // Fix that! ----
1548 SlotIndex NewMIIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(NewMI); 0
1549 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI->regunits(NewMI.getOperand(0).getReg())) 0
1550 if (LiveRange *LR = LIS->getCachedRegUnit(Unit)) 0
1551 LR->createDeadDef(NewMIIdx.getRegSlot(), LIS->getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
1552 } ----
1553 ----
1554 if (NewMI.getOperand(0).getSubReg()) 0
1555 NewMI.getOperand(0).setIsUndef(); 0
1556 ----
1557 // Transfer over implicit operands to the rematerialized instruction. ----
1558 for (MachineOperand &MO : ImplicitOps) 0
1559 NewMI.addOperand(MO); 0
1560 ----
1561 SlotIndex NewMIIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(NewMI); 0
1562 for (unsigned i = 0, e = NewMIImplDefs.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1563 MCRegister Reg = NewMIImplDefs[i]; 0
1564 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI->regunits(Reg)) 0
1565 if (LiveRange *LR = LIS->getCachedRegUnit(Unit)) 0
1566 LR->createDeadDef(NewMIIdx.getRegSlot(), LIS->getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
1567 } ----
1568 ----
1569 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Remat: " << NewMI); 0
1570 ++NumReMats; 0
1571 ----
1572 // If the virtual SrcReg is completely eliminated, update all DBG_VALUEs ----
1573 // to describe DstReg instead. ----
1574 if (MRI->use_nodbg_empty(SrcReg)) { 0
1575 for (MachineOperand &UseMO : 0
1576 llvm::make_early_inc_range(MRI->use_operands(SrcReg))) { 0
1577 MachineInstr *UseMI = UseMO.getParent(); 0
1578 if (UseMI->isDebugInstr()) { 0
1579 if (DstReg.isPhysical()) 0
1580 UseMO.substPhysReg(DstReg, *TRI); 0
1581 else ----
1582 UseMO.setReg(DstReg); 0
1583 // Move the debug value directly after the def of the rematerialized ----
1584 // value in DstReg. ----
1585 MBB->splice(std::next(NewMI.getIterator()), UseMI->getParent(), UseMI); 0
1586 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\t\tupdated: " << *UseMI); 0
1587 } ----
1588 } ----
1589 } ----
1590 ----
1591 if (ToBeUpdated.count(SrcReg)) 0
1592 return true; 0
1593 ----
1594 unsigned NumCopyUses = 0; 0
1595 for (MachineOperand &UseMO : MRI->use_nodbg_operands(SrcReg)) { 0
1596 if (UseMO.getParent()->isCopyLike()) 0
1597 NumCopyUses++; 0
1598 } ----
1599 if (NumCopyUses < LateRematUpdateThreshold) { 0
1600 // The source interval can become smaller because we removed a use. ----
1601 shrinkToUses(&SrcInt, &DeadDefs); 0
1602 if (!DeadDefs.empty()) 0
1603 eliminateDeadDefs(&Edit); 0
1604 } else { ----
1605 ToBeUpdated.insert(SrcReg); 0
1606 } ----
1607 return true; 0
1608 } 0
1609 ----
1610 MachineInstr *RegisterCoalescer::eliminateUndefCopy(MachineInstr *CopyMI) { 0
1611 // ProcessImplicitDefs may leave some copies of values, it only ----
1612 // removes local variables. When we have a copy like: ----
1613 // ----
1614 // %1 = COPY undef %2 ----
1615 // ----
1616 // We delete the copy and remove the corresponding value number from %1. ----
1617 // Any uses of that value number are marked as . ----
1618 ----
1619 // Note that we do not query CoalescerPair here but redo isMoveInstr as the ----
1620 // CoalescerPair may have a new register class with adjusted subreg indices ----
1621 // at this point. ----
1622 Register SrcReg, DstReg; 0
1623 unsigned SrcSubIdx = 0, DstSubIdx = 0; 0
1624 if(!isMoveInstr(*TRI, CopyMI, SrcReg, DstReg, SrcSubIdx, DstSubIdx)) 0
1625 return nullptr; 0
1626 ----
1627 SlotIndex Idx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(*CopyMI); 0
1628 const LiveInterval &SrcLI = LIS->getInterval(SrcReg); 0
1629 // CopyMI is undef iff SrcReg is not live before the instruction. ----
1630 if (SrcSubIdx != 0 && SrcLI.hasSubRanges()) { 0
1631 LaneBitmask SrcMask = TRI->getSubRegIndexLaneMask(SrcSubIdx); 0
1632 for (const LiveInterval::SubRange &SR : SrcLI.subranges()) { 0
1633 if ((SR.LaneMask & SrcMask).none()) 0
1634 continue; 0
1635 if (SR.liveAt(Idx)) 0
1636 return nullptr; 0
1637 } ----
1638 } else if (SrcLI.liveAt(Idx)) 0
1639 return nullptr; 0
1640 ----
1641 // If the undef copy defines a live-out value (i.e. an input to a PHI def), ----
1642 // then replace it with an IMPLICIT_DEF. ----
1643 LiveInterval &DstLI = LIS->getInterval(DstReg); 0
1644 SlotIndex RegIndex = Idx.getRegSlot(); 0
1645 LiveRange::Segment *Seg = DstLI.getSegmentContaining(RegIndex); 0
1646 assert(Seg != nullptr && "No segment for defining instruction"); 0
1647 VNInfo *V = DstLI.getVNInfoAt(Seg->end); 0
1648 ----
1649 // The source interval may also have been on an undef use, in which case the ----
1650 // copy introduced a live value. ----
1651 if (((V && V->isPHIDef()) || (!V && !DstLI.liveAt(Idx)))) { 0
1652 CopyMI->setDesc(TII->get(TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF)); 0
1653 for (unsigned i = CopyMI->getNumOperands(); i != 0; --i) { 0
1654 MachineOperand &MO = CopyMI->getOperand(i-1); 0
1655 if (MO.isReg() && MO.isUse()) 0
1656 CopyMI->removeOperand(i-1); 0
1657 } ----
1658 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tReplaced copy of value with an " 0
1659 "implicit def\n"); ----
1660 return CopyMI; 0
1661 } ----
1662 ----
1663 // Remove any DstReg segments starting at the instruction. ----
1664 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tEliminating copy of value\n"); 0
1665 ----
1666 // Remove value or merge with previous one in case of a subregister def. ----
1667 if (VNInfo *PrevVNI = DstLI.getVNInfoAt(Idx)) { 0
1668 VNInfo *VNI = DstLI.getVNInfoAt(RegIndex); 0
1669 DstLI.MergeValueNumberInto(VNI, PrevVNI); 0
1670 ----
1671 // The affected subregister segments can be removed. ----
1672 LaneBitmask DstMask = TRI->getSubRegIndexLaneMask(DstSubIdx); 0
1673 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &SR : DstLI.subranges()) { 0
1674 if ((SR.LaneMask & DstMask).none()) 0
1675 continue; 0
1676 ----
1677 VNInfo *SVNI = SR.getVNInfoAt(RegIndex); 0
1678 assert(SVNI != nullptr && SlotIndex::isSameInstr(SVNI->def, RegIndex)); 0
1679 SR.removeValNo(SVNI); 0
1680 } ----
1681 DstLI.removeEmptySubRanges(); 0
1682 } else ----
1683 LIS->removeVRegDefAt(DstLI, RegIndex); 0
1684 ----
1685 // Mark uses as undef. ----
1686 for (MachineOperand &MO : MRI->reg_nodbg_operands(DstReg)) { 0
1687 if (MO.isDef() /*|| MO.isUndef()*/) 0
1688 continue; 0
1689 const MachineInstr &MI = *MO.getParent(); 0
1690 SlotIndex UseIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(MI); 0
1691 LaneBitmask UseMask = TRI->getSubRegIndexLaneMask(MO.getSubReg()); 0
1692 bool isLive; ----
1693 if (!UseMask.all() && DstLI.hasSubRanges()) { 0
1694 isLive = false; 0
1695 for (const LiveInterval::SubRange &SR : DstLI.subranges()) { 0
1696 if ((SR.LaneMask & UseMask).none()) 0
1697 continue; 0
1698 if (SR.liveAt(UseIdx)) { 0
1699 isLive = true; 0
1700 break; 0
1701 } ----
1702 } ----
1703 } else ----
1704 isLive = DstLI.liveAt(UseIdx); 0
1705 if (isLive) 0
1706 continue; 0
1707 MO.setIsUndef(true); 0
1708 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tnew undef: " << UseIdx << '\t' << MI); 0
1709 } ----
1710 ----
1711 // A def of a subregister may be a use of the other subregisters, so ----
1712 // deleting a def of a subregister may also remove uses. Since CopyMI ----
1713 // is still part of the function (but about to be erased), mark all ----
1714 // defs of DstReg in it as , so that shrinkToUses would ----
1715 // ignore them. ----
1716 for (MachineOperand &MO : CopyMI->all_defs()) 0
1717 if (MO.getReg() == DstReg) 0
1718 MO.setIsUndef(true); 0
1719 LIS->shrinkToUses(&DstLI); 0
1720 ----
1721 return CopyMI; 0
1722 } ----
1723 ----
1724 void RegisterCoalescer::addUndefFlag(const LiveInterval &Int, SlotIndex UseIdx, 0
1725 MachineOperand &MO, unsigned SubRegIdx) { ----
1726 LaneBitmask Mask = TRI->getSubRegIndexLaneMask(SubRegIdx); 0
1727 if (MO.isDef()) 0
1728 Mask = ~Mask; 0
1729 bool IsUndef = true; 0
1730 for (const LiveInterval::SubRange &S : Int.subranges()) { 0
1731 if ((S.LaneMask & Mask).none()) 0
1732 continue; 0
1733 if (S.liveAt(UseIdx)) { 0
1734 IsUndef = false; 0
1735 break; 0
1736 } ----
1737 } ----
1738 if (IsUndef) { 0
1739 MO.setIsUndef(true); 0
1740 // We found out some subregister use is actually reading an undefined ----
1741 // value. In some cases the whole vreg has become undefined at this ----
1742 // point so we have to potentially shrink the main range if the ----
1743 // use was ending a live segment there. ----
1744 LiveQueryResult Q = Int.Query(UseIdx); 0
1745 if (Q.valueOut() == nullptr) 0
1746 ShrinkMainRange = true; 0
1747 } ----
1748 } 0
1749 ----
1750 void RegisterCoalescer::updateRegDefsUses(Register SrcReg, Register DstReg, 0
1751 unsigned SubIdx) { ----
1752 bool DstIsPhys = DstReg.isPhysical(); 0
1753 LiveInterval *DstInt = DstIsPhys ? nullptr : &LIS->getInterval(DstReg); 0
1754 ----
1755 if (DstInt && DstInt->hasSubRanges() && DstReg != SrcReg) { 0
1756 for (MachineOperand &MO : MRI->reg_operands(DstReg)) { 0
1757 unsigned SubReg = MO.getSubReg(); 0
1758 if (SubReg == 0 || MO.isUndef()) 0
1759 continue; 0
1760 MachineInstr &MI = *MO.getParent(); 0
1761 if (MI.isDebugInstr()) 0
1762 continue; 0
1763 SlotIndex UseIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(MI).getRegSlot(true); 0
1764 addUndefFlag(*DstInt, UseIdx, MO, SubReg); 0
1765 } ----
1766 } ----
1767 ----
1768 SmallPtrSet Visited; 0
1769 for (MachineRegisterInfo::reg_instr_iterator 0
1770 I = MRI->reg_instr_begin(SrcReg), E = MRI->reg_instr_end(); 0
1771 I != E; ) { 0
1772 MachineInstr *UseMI = &*(I++); 0
1773 ----
1774 // Each instruction can only be rewritten once because sub-register ----
1775 // composition is not always idempotent. When SrcReg != DstReg, rewriting ----
1776 // the UseMI operands removes them from the SrcReg use-def chain, but when ----
1777 // SrcReg is DstReg we could encounter UseMI twice if it has multiple ----
1778 // operands mentioning the virtual register. ----
1779 if (SrcReg == DstReg && !Visited.insert(UseMI).second) 0
1780 continue; 0
1781 ----
1782 SmallVector Ops; 0
1783 bool Reads, Writes; ----
1784 std::tie(Reads, Writes) = UseMI->readsWritesVirtualRegister(SrcReg, &Ops); 0
1785 ----
1786 // If SrcReg wasn't read, it may still be the case that DstReg is live-in ----
1787 // because SrcReg is a sub-register. ----
1788 if (DstInt && !Reads && SubIdx && !UseMI->isDebugInstr()) 0
1789 Reads = DstInt->liveAt(LIS->getInstructionIndex(*UseMI)); 0
1790 ----
1791 // Replace SrcReg with DstReg in all UseMI operands. ----
1792 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Ops.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1793 MachineOperand &MO = UseMI->getOperand(Ops[i]); 0
1794 ----
1795 // Adjust flags in case of sub-register joins. We don't want to ----
1796 // turn a full def into a read-modify-write sub-register def and vice ----
1797 // versa. ----
1798 if (SubIdx && MO.isDef()) 0
1799 MO.setIsUndef(!Reads); 0
1800 ----
1801 // A subreg use of a partially undef (super) register may be a complete ----
1802 // undef use now and then has to be marked that way. ----
1803 if (MO.isUse() && !DstIsPhys) { 0
1804 unsigned SubUseIdx = TRI->composeSubRegIndices(SubIdx, MO.getSubReg()); 0
1805 if (SubUseIdx != 0 && MRI->shouldTrackSubRegLiveness(DstReg)) { 0
1806 if (!DstInt->hasSubRanges()) { 0
1807 BumpPtrAllocator &Allocator = LIS->getVNInfoAllocator(); 0
1808 LaneBitmask FullMask = MRI->getMaxLaneMaskForVReg(DstInt->reg()); 0
1809 LaneBitmask UsedLanes = TRI->getSubRegIndexLaneMask(SubIdx); 0
1810 LaneBitmask UnusedLanes = FullMask & ~UsedLanes; 0
1811 DstInt->createSubRangeFrom(Allocator, UsedLanes, *DstInt); 0
1812 // The unused lanes are just empty live-ranges at this point. ----
1813 // It is the caller responsibility to set the proper ----
1814 // dead segments if there is an actual dead def of the ----
1815 // unused lanes. This may happen with rematerialization. ----
1816 DstInt->createSubRange(Allocator, UnusedLanes); 0
1817 } ----
1818 SlotIndex MIIdx = UseMI->isDebugInstr() 0
1819 ? LIS->getSlotIndexes()->getIndexBefore(*UseMI) 0
1820 : LIS->getInstructionIndex(*UseMI); 0
1821 SlotIndex UseIdx = MIIdx.getRegSlot(true); 0
1822 addUndefFlag(*DstInt, UseIdx, MO, SubUseIdx); 0
1823 } ----
1824 } ----
1825 ----
1826 if (DstIsPhys) 0
1827 MO.substPhysReg(DstReg, *TRI); 0
1828 else ----
1829 MO.substVirtReg(DstReg, SubIdx, *TRI); 0
1830 } ----
1831 ----
1832 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
1833 dbgs() << "\t\tupdated: "; ----
1834 if (!UseMI->isDebugInstr()) ----
1835 dbgs() << LIS->getInstructionIndex(*UseMI) << "\t"; ----
1836 dbgs() << *UseMI; ----
1837 }); ----
1838 } 0
1839 } 0

1841 bool RegisterCoalescer::canJoinPhys(const CoalescerPair &CP) { 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1842 // Always join simple intervals that are defined by a single copy from a ----
1843 // reserved register. This doesn't increase register pressure, so it is ----
1844 // always beneficial. ----
1845 if (!MRI->isReserved(CP.getDstReg())) { 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll

1848 } ----

1850 LiveInterval &JoinVInt = LIS->getInterval(CP.getSrcReg()); 0
1851 if (JoinVInt.containsOneValue()) 0
1852 return true; 0
1853 ----
1854 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1855 dbgs() << "\tCannot join complex intervals into reserved register.\n"); ----
1856 return false; 0

1858 ----
1859 bool RegisterCoalescer::copyValueUndefInPredecessors( 0
1860 LiveRange &S, const MachineBasicBlock *MBB, LiveQueryResult SLRQ) { ----
1861 for (const MachineBasicBlock *Pred : MBB->predecessors()) { 0
1862 SlotIndex PredEnd = LIS->getMBBEndIdx(Pred); 0
1863 if (VNInfo *V = S.getVNInfoAt(PredEnd.getPrevSlot())) { 0
1864 // If this is a self loop, we may be reading the same value. ----
1865 if (V->id != SLRQ.valueOutOrDead()->id) 0
1866 return false; 0
1867 } ----
1868 } ----
1869 ----
1870 return true; 0
1871 } ----
1872 ----
1873 void RegisterCoalescer::setUndefOnPrunedSubRegUses(LiveInterval &LI, 0
1874 Register Reg, ----
1875 LaneBitmask PrunedLanes) { ----
1876 // If we had other instructions in the segment reading the undef sublane ----
1877 // value, we need to mark them with undef. ----
1878 for (MachineOperand &MO : MRI->use_nodbg_operands(Reg)) { 0
1879 unsigned SubRegIdx = MO.getSubReg(); 0
1880 if (SubRegIdx == 0 || MO.isUndef()) 0
1881 continue; 0
1882 ----
1883 LaneBitmask SubRegMask = TRI->getSubRegIndexLaneMask(SubRegIdx); 0
1884 SlotIndex Pos = LIS->getInstructionIndex(*MO.getParent()); 0
1885 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &S : LI.subranges()) { 0
1886 if (!S.liveAt(Pos) && (PrunedLanes & SubRegMask).any()) { 0
1887 MO.setIsUndef(); 0
1888 break; 0
1889 } ----
1890 } ----
1891 } ----
1892 ----
1893 LI.removeEmptySubRanges(); 0
1894 ----
1895 // A def of a subregister may be a use of other register lanes. Replacing ----
1896 // such a def with a def of a different register will eliminate the use, ----
1897 // and may cause the recorded live range to be larger than the actual ----
1898 // liveness in the program IR. ----
1899 LIS->shrinkToUses(&LI); 0
1900 } 0

1902 bool RegisterCoalescer::joinCopy(MachineInstr *CopyMI, bool &Again) { 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1903 Again = false; 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1904 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << LIS->getInstructionIndex(*CopyMI) << '\t' << *CopyMI); 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1905 ----
1906 CoalescerPair CP(*TRI); 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1907 if (!CP.setRegisters(CopyMI)) { 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1908 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tNot coalescable.\n"); 0

1910 } ----
1911 ----
1912 if (CP.getNewRC()) { 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1913 auto SrcRC = MRI->getRegClass(CP.getSrcReg()); 0
1914 auto DstRC = MRI->getRegClass(CP.getDstReg()); 0
1915 unsigned SrcIdx = CP.getSrcIdx(); 0
1916 unsigned DstIdx = CP.getDstIdx(); 0
1917 if (CP.isFlipped()) { 0
1918 std::swap(SrcIdx, DstIdx); 0
1919 std::swap(SrcRC, DstRC); 0

1921 if (!TRI->shouldCoalesce(CopyMI, SrcRC, SrcIdx, DstRC, DstIdx, 0
1922 CP.getNewRC(), *LIS)) { 0
1923 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tSubtarget bailed on coalescing.\n"); 0

1926 } ----
1927 ----

1929 // sometimes dead copies slip through, and we can't generate invalid live ----
1930 // ranges. ----
1931 if (!CP.isPhys() && CopyMI->allDefsAreDead()) { 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1932 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tCopy is dead.\n"); 0
1933 DeadDefs.push_back(CopyMI); 0
1934 eliminateDeadDefs(); 0
1935 return true; 0
1936 } ----
1937 ----
1938 // Eliminate undefs. ----
1939 if (!CP.isPhys()) { 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1940 // If this is an IMPLICIT_DEF, leave it alone, but don't try to coalesce. ----
1941 if (MachineInstr *UndefMI = eliminateUndefCopy(CopyMI)) { 0
1942 if (UndefMI->isImplicitDef()) 0
1943 return false; 0
1944 deleteInstr(CopyMI); 0
1945 return false; // Not coalescable. 0
1946 } ----
1947 } ----
1948 ----
1949 // Coalesced copies are normally removed immediately, but transformations ----
1950 // like removeCopyByCommutingDef() can inadvertently create identity copies. ----
1951 // When that happens, just join the values and remove the copy. ----
1952 if (CP.getSrcReg() == CP.getDstReg()) { 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1953 LiveInterval &LI = LIS->getInterval(CP.getSrcReg()); 0
1954 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tCopy already coalesced: " << LI << '\n'); 0
1955 const SlotIndex CopyIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(*CopyMI); 0
1956 LiveQueryResult LRQ = LI.Query(CopyIdx); 0
1957 if (VNInfo *DefVNI = LRQ.valueDefined()) { 0
1958 VNInfo *ReadVNI = LRQ.valueIn(); 0
1959 assert(ReadVNI && "No value before copy and no flag."); 0
1960 assert(ReadVNI != DefVNI && "Cannot read and define the same value."); 0
1961 ----
1962 // Track incoming undef lanes we need to eliminate from the subrange. ----
1963 LaneBitmask PrunedLanes; 0
1964 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = CopyMI->getParent(); 0
1965 ----
1966 // Process subregister liveranges. ----
1967 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &S : LI.subranges()) { 0
1968 LiveQueryResult SLRQ = S.Query(CopyIdx); 0
1969 if (VNInfo *SDefVNI = SLRQ.valueDefined()) { 0
1970 if (VNInfo *SReadVNI = SLRQ.valueIn()) 0
1971 SDefVNI = S.MergeValueNumberInto(SDefVNI, SReadVNI); 0
1972 ----
1973 // If this copy introduced an undef subrange from an incoming value, ----
1974 // we need to eliminate the undef live in values from the subrange. ----
1975 if (copyValueUndefInPredecessors(S, MBB, SLRQ)) { 0
1976 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Incoming sublane value is undef at copy\n"); 0
1977 PrunedLanes |= S.LaneMask; 0
1978 S.removeValNo(SDefVNI); 0
1979 } ----
1980 } ----
1981 } ----
1982 ----
1983 LI.MergeValueNumberInto(DefVNI, ReadVNI); 0
1984 if (PrunedLanes.any()) { 0
1985 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Pruning undef incoming lanes: " 0
1986 << PrunedLanes << '\n'); ----
1987 setUndefOnPrunedSubRegUses(LI, CP.getSrcReg(), PrunedLanes); 0
1988 } ----
1989 ----
1990 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tMerged values: " << LI << '\n'); 0
1991 } ----
1992 deleteInstr(CopyMI); 0
1993 return true; 0
1994 } ----
1995 ----
1996 // Enforce policies. ----
1997 if (CP.isPhys()) { 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1998 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tConsidering merging " 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
1999 << printReg(CP.getSrcReg(), TRI) << " with " ----
2000 << printReg(CP.getDstReg(), TRI, CP.getSrcIdx()) << '\n'); ----
2001 if (!canJoinPhys(CP)) { 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2002 // Before giving up coalescing, if definition of source is defined by ----
2003 // trivial computation, try rematerializing it. ----
2004 bool IsDefCopy = false; 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2005 if (reMaterializeTrivialDef(CP, CopyMI, IsDefCopy)) 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2006 return true; 0
2007 if (IsDefCopy) 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2008 Again = true; // May be possible to coalesce later. 0
2009 return false; 6 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
2010 } ----
2011 } else { ----
2012 // When possible, let DstReg be the larger interval. ----
2013 if (!CP.isPartial() && LIS->getInterval(CP.getSrcReg()).size() > 0
2014 LIS->getInterval(CP.getDstReg()).size()) 0
2015 CP.flip(); 0
2016 ----
2017 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
2018 dbgs() << "\tConsidering merging to " ----
2019 << TRI->getRegClassName(CP.getNewRC()) << " with "; ----
2020 if (CP.getDstIdx() && CP.getSrcIdx()) ----
2021 dbgs() << printReg(CP.getDstReg()) << " in " ----
2022 << TRI->getSubRegIndexName(CP.getDstIdx()) << " and " ----
2023 << printReg(CP.getSrcReg()) << " in " ----
2024 << TRI->getSubRegIndexName(CP.getSrcIdx()) << '\n'; ----
2025 else ----
2026 dbgs() << printReg(CP.getSrcReg(), TRI) << " in " ----
2027 << printReg(CP.getDstReg(), TRI, CP.getSrcIdx()) << '\n'; ----
2028 }); ----
2029 } ----
2030 ----
2031 ShrinkMask = LaneBitmask::getNone(); 0
2032 ShrinkMainRange = false; 0
2033 ----
2034 // Okay, attempt to join these two intervals. On failure, this returns false. ----
2035 // Otherwise, if one of the intervals being joined is a physreg, this method ----
2036 // always canonicalizes DstInt to be it. The output "SrcInt" will not have ----
2037 // been modified, so we can use this information below to update aliases. ----
2038 if (!joinIntervals(CP)) { 0
2039 // Coalescing failed. ----
2040 ----
2041 // If definition of source is defined by trivial computation, try ----
2042 // rematerializing it. ----
2043 bool IsDefCopy = false; 0
2044 if (reMaterializeTrivialDef(CP, CopyMI, IsDefCopy)) 0
2045 return true; 0
2046 ----
2047 // If we can eliminate the copy without merging the live segments, do so ----
2048 // now. ----
2049 if (!CP.isPartial() && !CP.isPhys()) { 0
2050 bool Changed = adjustCopiesBackFrom(CP, CopyMI); 0
2051 bool Shrink = false; 0
2052 if (!Changed) 0
2053 std::tie(Changed, Shrink) = removeCopyByCommutingDef(CP, CopyMI); 0
2054 if (Changed) { 0
2055 deleteInstr(CopyMI); 0
2056 if (Shrink) { 0
2057 Register DstReg = CP.isFlipped() ? CP.getSrcReg() : CP.getDstReg(); 0
2058 LiveInterval &DstLI = LIS->getInterval(DstReg); 0
2059 shrinkToUses(&DstLI); 0
2060 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\t\tshrunk: " << DstLI << '\n'); 0
2061 } ----
2062 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tTrivial!\n"); 0
2063 return true; 0
2064 } ----
2065 } ----
2066 ----
2067 // Try and see if we can partially eliminate the copy by moving the copy to ----
2068 // its predecessor. ----
2069 if (!CP.isPartial() && !CP.isPhys()) 0
2070 if (removePartialRedundancy(CP, *CopyMI)) 0
2071 return true; 0
2072 ----
2073 // Otherwise, we are unable to join the intervals. ----
2074 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tInterference!\n"); 0
2075 Again = true; // May be possible to coalesce later. 0
2076 return false; 0
2077 } ----
2078 ----
2079 // Coalescing to a virtual register that is of a sub-register class of the ----
2080 // other. Make sure the resulting register is set to the right register class. ----
2081 if (CP.isCrossClass()) { 0
2082 ++numCrossRCs; 0
2083 MRI->setRegClass(CP.getDstReg(), CP.getNewRC()); 0
2084 } ----
2085 ----
2086 // Removing sub-register copies can ease the register class constraints. ----
2087 // Make sure we attempt to inflate the register class of DstReg. ----
2088 if (!CP.isPhys() && RegClassInfo.isProperSubClass(CP.getNewRC())) 0
2089 InflateRegs.push_back(CP.getDstReg()); 0
2090 ----
2091 // CopyMI has been erased by joinIntervals at this point. Remove it from ----
2092 // ErasedInstrs since copyCoalesceWorkList() won't add a successful join back ----
2093 // to the work list. This keeps ErasedInstrs from growing needlessly. ----
2094 ErasedInstrs.erase(CopyMI); 0
2095 ----
2096 // Rewrite all SrcReg operands to DstReg. ----
2097 // Also update DstReg operands to include DstIdx if it is set. ----
2098 if (CP.getDstIdx()) 0
2099 updateRegDefsUses(CP.getDstReg(), CP.getDstReg(), CP.getDstIdx()); 0
2100 updateRegDefsUses(CP.getSrcReg(), CP.getDstReg(), CP.getSrcIdx()); 0
2101 ----
2102 // Shrink subregister ranges if necessary. ----
2103 if (ShrinkMask.any()) { 0
2104 LiveInterval &LI = LIS->getInterval(CP.getDstReg()); 0
2105 for (LiveInterval::SubRange &S : LI.subranges()) { 0
2106 if ((S.LaneMask & ShrinkMask).none()) 0
2107 continue; 0
2108 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Shrink LaneUses (Lane " << PrintLaneMask(S.LaneMask) 0
2109 << ")\n"); ----
2110 LIS->shrinkToUses(S, LI.reg()); 0
2111 ShrinkMainRange = true; 0
2112 } ----
2113 LI.removeEmptySubRanges(); 0
2114 } ----
2115 ----
2116 // CP.getSrcReg()'s live interval has been merged into CP.getDstReg's live ----
2117 // interval. Since CP.getSrcReg() is in ToBeUpdated set and its live interval ----
2118 // is not up-to-date, need to update the merged live interval here. ----
2119 if (ToBeUpdated.count(CP.getSrcReg())) 0
2120 ShrinkMainRange = true; 0
2121 ----
2122 if (ShrinkMainRange) { 0
2123 LiveInterval &LI = LIS->getInterval(CP.getDstReg()); 0
2124 shrinkToUses(&LI); 0
2125 } ----
2126 ----
2127 // SrcReg is guaranteed to be the register whose live interval that is ----
2128 // being merged. ----
2129 LIS->removeInterval(CP.getSrcReg()); 0
2130 ----
2131 // Update regalloc hint. ----
2132 TRI->updateRegAllocHint(CP.getSrcReg(), CP.getDstReg(), *MF); 0
2133 ----
2134 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
2135 dbgs() << "\tSuccess: " << printReg(CP.getSrcReg(), TRI, CP.getSrcIdx()) ----
2136 << " -> " << printReg(CP.getDstReg(), TRI, CP.getDstIdx()) << '\n'; ----
2137 dbgs() << "\tResult = "; ----
2138 if (CP.isPhys()) ----
2139 dbgs() << printReg(CP.getDstReg(), TRI); ----
2140 else ----
2141 dbgs() << LIS->getInterval(CP.getDstReg()); ----
2142 dbgs() << '\n'; ----
2143 }); ----
2144 ----
2145 ++numJoins; 0
2146 return true; 0
2147 } ----
2148 ----
2149 bool RegisterCoalescer::joinReservedPhysReg(CoalescerPair &CP) { 0
2150 Register DstReg = CP.getDstReg(); 0
2151 Register SrcReg = CP.getSrcReg(); 0
2152 assert(CP.isPhys() && "Must be a physreg copy"); 0
2153 assert(MRI->isReserved(DstReg) && "Not a reserved register"); 0
2154 LiveInterval &RHS = LIS->getInterval(SrcReg); 0
2155 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\t\tRHS = " << RHS << '\n'); 0
2156 ----
2157 assert(RHS.containsOneValue() && "Invalid join with reserved register"); 0
2158 ----
2159 // Optimization for reserved registers like ESP. We can only merge with a ----
2160 // reserved physreg if RHS has a single value that is a copy of DstReg. ----
2161 // The live range of the reserved register will look like a set of dead defs ----
2162 // - we don't properly track the live range of reserved registers. ----
2163 ----
2164 // Deny any overlapping intervals. This depends on all the reserved ----
2165 // register live ranges to look like dead defs. ----
2166 if (!MRI->isConstantPhysReg(DstReg)) { 0
2167 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI->regunits(DstReg)) { 0
2168 // Abort if not all the regunits are reserved. ----
2169 for (MCRegUnitRootIterator RI(Unit, TRI); RI.isValid(); ++RI) { 0
2170 if (!MRI->isReserved(*RI)) 0
2171 return false; 0
2172 } ----
2173 if (RHS.overlaps(LIS->getRegUnit(Unit))) { 0
2174 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\t\tInterference: " << printRegUnit(Unit, TRI) 0
2175 << '\n'); ----
2176 return false; 0
2177 } ----
2178 } ----
2179 ----
2180 // We must also check for overlaps with regmask clobbers. ----
2181 BitVector RegMaskUsable; 0
2182 if (LIS->checkRegMaskInterference(RHS, RegMaskUsable) && 0
2183 !RegMaskUsable.test(DstReg)) { 0
2184 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\t\tRegMask interference\n"); 0
2185 return false; 0
2186 } ----
2187 } 0
2188 ----
2189 // Skip any value computations, we are not adding new values to the ----
2190 // reserved register. Also skip merging the live ranges, the reserved ----
2191 // register live range doesn't need to be accurate as long as all the ----
2192 // defs are there. ----
2193 ----
2194 // Delete the identity copy. ----
2195 MachineInstr *CopyMI; ----
2196 if (CP.isFlipped()) { 0
2197 // Physreg is copied into vreg ----
2198 // %y = COPY %physreg_x ----
2199 // ... //< no other def of %physreg_x here ----
2200 // use %y ----
2201 // => ----
2202 // ... ----
2203 // use %physreg_x ----
2204 CopyMI = MRI->getVRegDef(SrcReg); 0
2205 deleteInstr(CopyMI); 0
2206 } else { ----
2207 // VReg is copied into physreg: ----
2208 // %y = def ----
2209 // ... //< no other def or use of %physreg_x here ----
2210 // %physreg_x = COPY %y ----
2211 // => ----
2212 // %physreg_x = def ----
2213 // ... ----
2214 if (!MRI->hasOneNonDBGUse(SrcReg)) { 0
2215 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\t\tMultiple vreg uses!\n"); 0
2216 return false; 0
2217 } ----
2218 ----
2219 if (!LIS->intervalIsInOneMBB(RHS)) { 0
2220 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\t\tComplex control flow!\n"); 0
2221 return false; 0
2222 } ----
2223 ----
2224 MachineInstr &DestMI = *MRI->getVRegDef(SrcReg); 0
2225 CopyMI = &*MRI->use_instr_nodbg_begin(SrcReg); 0
2226 SlotIndex CopyRegIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(*CopyMI).getRegSlot(); 0
2227 SlotIndex DestRegIdx = LIS->getInstructionIndex(DestMI).getRegSlot(); 0
2228 ----
2229 if (!MRI->isConstantPhysReg(DstReg)) { 0
2230 // We checked above that there are no interfering defs of the physical ----
2231 // register. However, for this case, where we intend to move up the def of ----
2232 // the physical register, we also need to check for interfering uses. ----
2233 SlotIndexes *Indexes = LIS->getSlotIndexes(); 0
2234 for (SlotIndex SI = Indexes->getNextNonNullIndex(DestRegIdx); 0
2235 SI != CopyRegIdx; SI = Indexes->getNextNonNullIndex(SI)) { 0
2236 MachineInstr *MI = LIS->getInstructionFromIndex(SI); 0
2237 if (MI->readsRegister(DstReg, TRI)) { 0
2238 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\t\tInterference (read): " << *MI); 0
2239 return false; 0
2240 } ----
2241 } ----
2242 } ----
2243 ----
2244 // We're going to remove the copy which defines a physical reserved ----
2245 // register, so remove its valno, etc. ----
2246 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\t\tRemoving phys reg def of " 0
2247 << printReg(DstReg, TRI) << " at " << CopyRegIdx << "\n"); ----
2248 ----
2249 LIS->removePhysRegDefAt(DstReg.asMCReg(), CopyRegIdx); 0
2250 deleteInstr(CopyMI); 0
2251 ----
2252 // Create a new dead def at the new def location. ----
2253 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI->regunits(DstReg)) { 0
2254 LiveRange &LR = LIS->getRegUnit(Unit); 0
2255 LR.createDeadDef(DestRegIdx, LIS->getVNInfoAllocator()); 0
2256 } ----
2257 } ----
2258 ----
2259 // We don't track kills for reserved registers. ----
2260 MRI->clearKillFlags(CP.getSrcReg()); 0
2261 ----
2262 return true; 0
2263 } ----
2264 ----
2265 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2266 // Interference checking and interval joining ----
2267 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
2268 // ----
2269 // In the easiest case, the two live ranges being joined are disjoint, and ----
2270 // there is no interference to consider. It is quite common, though, to have ----
2271 // overlapping live ranges, and we need to check if the interference can be ----
2272 // resolved. ----
2273 // ----
2274 // The live range of a single SSA value forms a sub-tree of the dominator tree. ----
2275 // This means that two SSA values overlap if and only if the def of one value ----
2276 // is contained in the live range of the other value. As a special case, the ----
2277 // overlapping values can be defined at the same index. ----
2278 // ----
2279 // The interference from an overlapping def can be resolved in these cases: ----
2280 // ----
2281 // 1. Coalescable copies. The value is defined by a copy that would become an ----
2282 // identity copy after joining SrcReg and DstReg. The copy instruction will ----
2283 // be removed, and the value will be merged with the source value. ----
2284 // ----
2285 // There can be several copies back and forth, causing many values to be ----
2286 // merged into one. We compute a list of ultimate values in the joined live ----
2287 // range as well as a mappings from the old value numbers. ----
2288 // ----
2289 // 2. IMPLICIT_DEF. This instruction is only inserted to ensure all PHI ----
2290 // predecessors have a live out value. It doesn't cause real interference, ----
2291 // and can be merged into the value it overlaps. Like a coalescable copy, it ----
2292 // can be erased after joining. ----
2293 // ----
2294 // 3. Copy of external value. The overlapping def may be a copy of a value that ----
2295 // is already in the other register. This is like a coalescable copy, but ----
2296 // the live range of the source register must be trimmed after erasing the ----
2297 // copy instruction: ----
2298 // ----
2299 // %src = COPY %ext ----
2300 // %dst = COPY %ext <-- Remove this COPY, trim the live range of %ext. ----
2301 // ----
2302 // 4. Clobbering undefined lanes. Vector registers are sometimes built by ----
2303 // defining one lane at a time: ----
2304 // ----
2305 // %dst:ssub0 = FOO ----
2306 // %src = BAR ----
2307 // %dst:ssub1 = COPY %src ----
2308 // ----
2309 // The live range of %src overlaps the %dst value defined by FOO, but ----
2310 // merging %src into %dst:ssub1 is only going to clobber the ssub1 lane ----
2311 // which was undef anyway. ----
2312 // ----
2313 // The value mapping is more complicated in this case. The final live range ----
2314 // will have different value numbers for both FOO and BAR, but there is no ----
2315 // simple mapping from old to new values. It may even be necessary to add ----
2316 // new PHI values. ----
2317 // ----
2318 // 5. Clobbering dead lanes. A def may clobber a lane of a vector register that ----
2319 // is live, but never read. This can happen because we don't compute ----
2320 // individual live ranges per lane. ----
2321 // ----
2322 // %dst = FOO ----
2323 // %src = BAR ----
2324 // %dst:ssub1 = COPY %src ----
2325 // ----
2326 // This kind of interference is only resolved locally. If the clobbered ----
2327 // lane value escapes the block, the join is aborted. ----
2328 ----
2329 namespace { ----
2330 ----
2331 /// Track information about values in a single virtual register about to be ----
2332 /// joined. Objects of this class are always created in pairs - one for each ----
2333 /// side of the CoalescerPair (or one for each lane of a side of the coalescer ----
2334 /// pair) ----
2335 class JoinVals { ----
2336 /// Live range we work on. ----
2337 LiveRange &LR; ----
2338 ----
2339 /// (Main) register we work on. ----
2340 const Register Reg; ----
2341 ----
2342 /// Reg (and therefore the values in this liverange) will end up as ----
2343 /// subregister SubIdx in the coalesced register. Either CP.DstIdx or ----
2344 /// CP.SrcIdx. ----
2345 const unsigned SubIdx; ----
2346 ----
2347 /// The LaneMask that this liverange will occupy the coalesced register. May ----
2348 /// be smaller than the lanemask produced by SubIdx when merging subranges. ----
2349 const LaneBitmask LaneMask; ----
2350 ----
2351 /// This is true when joining sub register ranges, false when joining main ----
2352 /// ranges. ----
2353 const bool SubRangeJoin; ----
2354 ----
2355 /// Whether the current LiveInterval tracks subregister liveness. ----
2356 const bool TrackSubRegLiveness; ----
2357 ----
2358 /// Values that will be present in the final live range. ----
2359 SmallVectorImpl &NewVNInfo; ----
2360 ----
2361 const CoalescerPair &CP; ----
2362 LiveIntervals *LIS; ----
2363 SlotIndexes *Indexes; ----
2364 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI; ----
2365 ----
2366 /// Value number assignments. Maps value numbers in LI to entries in ----
2367 /// NewVNInfo. This is suitable for passing to LiveInterval::join(). ----
2368 SmallVector Assignments; ----
2369 ----
2370 public: ----
2371 /// Conflict resolution for overlapping values. ----
2372 enum ConflictResolution { ----
2373 /// No overlap, simply keep this value. ----
2374 CR_Keep, ----
2375 ----
2376 /// Merge this value into OtherVNI and erase the defining instruction. ----
2377 /// Used for IMPLICIT_DEF, coalescable copies, and copies from external ----
2378 /// values. ----
2379 CR_Erase, ----
2380 ----
2381 /// Merge this value into OtherVNI but keep the defining instruction. ----
2382 /// This is for the special case where OtherVNI is defined by the same ----
2383 /// instruction. ----
2384 CR_Merge, ----
2385 ----
2386 /// Keep this value, and have it replace OtherVNI where possible. This ----
2387 /// complicates value mapping since OtherVNI maps to two different values ----
2388 /// before and after this def. ----
2389 /// Used when clobbering undefined or dead lanes. ----
2390 CR_Replace, ----
2391 ----
2392 /// Unresolved conflict. Visit later when all values have been mapped. ----
2393 CR_Unresolved, ----
2394 ----
2395 /// Unresolvable conflict. Abort the join. ----
2396 CR_Impossible ----
2397 }; ----

2399 private: ----
2400 /// Per-value info for LI. The lane bit masks are all relative to the final ----
2401 /// joined register, so they can be compared directly between SrcReg and ----
2402 /// DstReg. ----
2403 struct Val { ----
2404 ConflictResolution Resolution = CR_Keep; ----
2405 ----
2406 /// Lanes written by this def, 0 for unanalyzed values. ----
2407 LaneBitmask WriteLanes; ----
2408 ----
2409 /// Lanes with defined values in this register. Other lanes are undef and ----
2410 /// safe to clobber. ----
2411 LaneBitmask ValidLanes; ----
2412 ----
2413 /// Value in LI being redefined by this def. ----
2414 VNInfo *RedefVNI = nullptr; ----
2415 ----
2416 /// Value in the other live range that overlaps this def, if any. ----
2417 VNInfo *OtherVNI = nullptr; ----
2418 ----
2419 /// Is this value an IMPLICIT_DEF that can be erased? ----
2420 /// ----
2421 /// IMPLICIT_DEF values should only exist at the end of a basic block that ----
2422 /// is a predecessor to a phi-value. These IMPLICIT_DEF instructions can be ----
2423 /// safely erased if they are overlapping a live value in the other live ----
2424 /// interval. ----
2425 /// ----
2426 /// Weird control flow graphs and incomplete PHI handling in ----
2427 /// ProcessImplicitDefs can very rarely create IMPLICIT_DEF values with ----
2428 /// longer live ranges. Such IMPLICIT_DEF values should be treated like ----
2429 /// normal values. ----
2430 bool ErasableImplicitDef = false; ----
2431 ----
2432 /// True when the live range of this value will be pruned because of an ----
2433 /// overlapping CR_Replace value in the other live range. ----
2434 bool Pruned = false; ----
2435 ----
2436 /// True once Pruned above has been computed. ----
2437 bool PrunedComputed = false; ----
2438 ----
2439 /// True if this value is determined to be identical to OtherVNI ----
2440 /// (in valuesIdentical). This is used with CR_Erase where the erased ----
2441 /// copy is redundant, i.e. the source value is already the same as ----
2442 /// the destination. In such cases the subranges need to be updated ----
2443 /// properly. See comment at pruneSubRegValues for more info. ----
2444 bool Identical = false; ----
2445 ----
2446 Val() = default; 0
2447 ----
2448 bool isAnalyzed() const { return WriteLanes.any(); } 0
2449 }; ----

2467 /// Recursively calls computeAssignment() on this and Other, guaranteeing that ----

2479 /// the extent of the tainted lanes in the block. ----
2480 /// ----
2481 /// Multiple values in Other.LR can be affected since partial redefinitions ----
2482 /// can preserve previously tainted lanes. ----
2483 /// ----
2484 /// 1 %dst = VLOAD <-- Define all lanes in %dst ----
2485 /// 2 %src = FOO <-- ValNo to be joined with %dst:ssub0 ----

2487 /// 4 %dst:ssub0 = COPY %src <-- Conflict resolved, ssub0 wasn't read ----
